About CVS
---------

0) Set the variable CVS_RHS to ssh ('export CVS_RHS=ssh' with bash, or
   'setenv CVS_RHS ssh' with tcsh)
   
1) The first time you want to download the latest full source by
   CVS, type:

   cvs -d username@cvs.geuz.org:/cvsroot ckeckout getdp

   where username is your login on cvs.geuz.org

2) To update your local version to the latest and greatest, go in the
   getdp directory and type:
 
   cvs update -dPA

3) To commit your changes to the central repository, go in the getdp
   directory and type:

   cvs commit


Developing in GetDP
--------------------

Some easy rules to make the code easy to read/debug/maintain:
- enable full warnings for your compiler (e.g. gcc -Wall)
- always use Msg() to print information/errors/etc.
- begin any new function with GetDP_Begin("function_name") and end
  it with GetDP_End or GetDP_Return(value). Never use 'return'
  directly.
- if working under Microsoft Windows, please indent your files and
  suppress the tabs before committing your changes (untabify)

